thread.title_full: DIARY - Today in Washington - Aug 11 | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: DIARY - Today in Washington - Aug 11
text:
ALL TIMES IN EDT/GMT
0600/1000: The National Federation of Independent Business issues Small Business Optimism Index for July.
0830/1230: The Labor Department issues Preliminary (1st Estimate) U.S. Q1 Nonfarm Productivity and Costs.
1000/1400: The Commerce Department issues Wholesale Inventories for June.
1130/1530: The Treasury Department holds weekly sale of 4-week bills.
1300/1700: The Treasury Department sells 3-year notes.
1630/2030: The American Petroleum Institute issues weekly national petroleum report.
